shrimp salad, shrimp and potatoes,

461
00:35:11,736 --> 00:35:14,780
shrimp burger, shrimp sandwich...

462
00:35:17,366 --> 00:35:19,702
That's... That's about it.

463
00:35:23,414 --> 00:35:26,375
<i>FORREST: Night time in the Army
is a lonely time.</i>

464
00:35:27,251 --> 00:35:30,880
<i>We'd lay there in our bunks
and I'd miss my mama.</i>

465
00:35:31,464 --> 00:35:33,966
<i>And I'd miss Jenny.</i>

466
00:35:37,887 --> 00:35:41,766
Hey, Gump, get a load of the tits on her!

467
00:35:55,237 --> 00:35:58,366
<i>Turns out, Jenny had gotten into
some trouble over</i>

468
00:35:58,449 --> 00:36:01,786
<i>some photos of her
in her college sweater,</i>

469
00:36:01,911 --> 00:36:04,455
<i>and she was thrown out of school.</i>

470
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:10,211
<i>But that wasn't a bad thing,</i>

471
00:36:10,294 --> 00:36:13,881
<i>because a man who owns
a theatre in Memphis, Tennessee,</i>

472
00:36:13,964 --> 00:36:19,011
<i>saw those photos and offered Jenny
a job singing in a show.</i>

473
00:36:19,804 --> 00:36:21,639
<i>The first chance I got,</i>

474
00:36:21,764 --> 00:36:25,434
<i>I took the bus up to Memphis
to see her perform in that show.</i>

475
00:36:25,518 --> 00:36:27,019
<i>That was Amber, Amber Flame.</i>

476
00:36:27,103 --> 00:36:29,563
<i>Give her a big hand, guys.
Good job, Amber.</i>

477
00:36:29,647 --> 00:36:32,400
<i>And now, for your listening
and viewing pleasure,</i>

478
00:36:32,483 --> 00:36:36,320
<i>direct from Hollywood, California,
our very own beatnik beauty,</i>

479
00:36:36,445 --> 00:36:40,116
<i>let's give a big round of applause
to the luscious Bobbi Dylan.</i>

480
00:36:40,366 --> 00:36:42,201
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

481
00:36:42,284 --> 00:36:44,537
MAN 1: All right!
MAN 2: Bobbi!

482
00:36:49,417 --> 00:36:54,088
(SINGING <i>BLOWIN' IN THE WIND)</i>

483
00:37:07,476 --> 00:37:09,562
<i>Her dream had come true.</i>

484
00:37:10,813 --> 00:37:12,815
<i>She was a folk singer.</i>

485
00:37:22,074 --> 00:37:24,326
MAN 3: Come on, baby. Shake it up.
Shake it up, now.

486
00:37:24,410 --> 00:37:25,911
MAN 4: Hey, buddy, get her a harmonica.

487
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:27,705
(CROWD LAUGHING)

488
00:37:29,665 --> 00:37:31,709
MAN 1: Hey, honey,
this ain't <i>Captain Kangaroo.</i>

489
00:37:31,834 --> 00:37:34,378
Hey, honey,
I got something here for you.

490
00:37:35,421 --> 00:37:39,175
- God damn it!
- Hey! Hey! Stupid jerk!

491
00:37:39,258 --> 00:37:41,719
I'm singing a song here.

492
00:37:44,054 --> 00:37:46,474
Polly, get out here!

493
00:37:46,557 --> 00:37:48,267
- Shut up, there!
- MAN 2: Don't be so shy, honey.

494
00:37:48,350 --> 00:37:49,894
JENNY: Oh, shut up!

495
00:37:52,563 --> 00:37:55,316
Forrest, what are you doing here?

496
00:37:55,399 --> 00:37:57,109
- What are you doing?
- MAN 3: Hey!

497
00:37:57,193 --> 00:37:58,569
- Come on.
- What are you doing?

498
00:37:58,694 --> 00:38:00,696
Forrest, let me down!

499
00:38:02,031 --> 00:38:03,032
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)

500
00:38:06,535 --> 00:38:08,454
You can't keep doing this, Forrest.

501
00:38:08,537 --> 00:38:10,623
You can't keep trying
to rescue me all the time.

502
00:38:10,706 --> 00:38:14,794
- They was trying to grab you.
- A lot of people try to grab me.

503
00:38:15,711 --> 00:38:18,881
Just... You can't keep
doing this all the time.

504
00:38:19,381 --> 00:38:22,301
I can't help it. I love you.

505
00:38:23,260 --> 00:38:26,764
Forrest, you don't know what love is.

506
00:38:34,063 --> 00:38:37,066
You remember that time
we prayed, Forrest?

507
00:38:37,942 --> 00:38:42,446
We prayed for God to turn me
into a bird so I could fly far, far away?

508
00:38:44,406 --> 00:38:45,783
Yes, I do.

509
00:38:49,745 --> 00:38:52,581
You think I could fly off this bridge?

510
00:38:59,255 --> 00:39:01,423
What do you mean, Jenny?

511
00:39:05,302 --> 00:39:06,804
Nothing.

512
00:39:09,765 --> 00:39:11,809
I gotta get out of here.

513
00:39:14,103 --> 00:39:15,187
Wait, Jenny...

514
00:39:15,271 --> 00:39:19,733
Forrest, you stay away from me, okay?
You just stay away from me, please.

515
00:39:19,817 --> 00:39:21,110
Can I have a ride?

516
00:39:21,193 --> 00:39:22,736
- MAN: Where you going?
- I don't care.

517
00:39:22,820 --> 00:39:24,196
Get in the truck.

518
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:26,115
So, bye-bye, Jenny.

519
00:39:28,617 --> 00:39:30,953
They sending me to Vietnam.

520
00:39:33,706 --> 00:39:36,125
It's this whole other country.

521
00:39:38,627 --> 00:39:40,629
Just hang on a minute.

522
00:39:42,047 --> 00:39:45,092
Listen, you promise me
something, okay?

523
00:39:45,175 --> 00:39:48,512
Just, if you're ever in trouble,
don't try to be brave. You just run, okay?

524
00:39:48,637 --> 00:39:50,222
Just run away.

525
00:39:51,473 --> 00:39:52,808
Okay.

526
00:39:57,688 --> 00:39:59,023
Jenny.

527
00:40:00,900 --> 00:40:03,193
I'll write you all the time.

528
00:40:12,328 --> 00:40:15,331
<i>FORREST: And just like that,
she was gone.</i>

529
00:40:31,430 --> 00:40:34,767
You come back safe to me,
do you hear?

530
00:41:18,060 --> 00:41:22,022
<i>Now, they told us that Vietnam
was gonna be very different</i>

531
00:41:22,106 --> 00:41:24,984
<i>from the United States of America.</i>

532
00:41:25,067 --> 00:41:30,114
<i>And except for all the beer cans
and the barbecue, it was.</i>

533
00:41:40,249 --> 00:41:43,335
Hey, I bet there's shrimp
all in these waters.

534
00:41:43,419 --> 00:41:46,588
They tell me these Vietnams
is good shrimpers.

535
00:41:46,672 --> 00:41:50,217
You know, after we win this war,
and we take over everything,

536
00:41:50,300 --> 00:41:51,510
we can get American shrimpers

537
00:41:51,593 --> 00:41:53,345
to come out here
and shrimp these waters.

538
00:41:53,429 --> 00:41:54,972
We'll just shrimp all the time, man.

539
00:41:55,097 --> 00:41:58,267
So much shrimp, why,
you wouldn't believe it.

540
00:41:58,934 --> 00:42:00,853
You must be my FNGs.

541
00:42:00,936 --> 00:42:02,187
- Morning, sir!
- Morning, sir!

542
00:42:02,271 --> 00:42:04,898
Get your hands down! Do not salute me.

543
00:42:04,982 --> 00:42:07,109
There's goddamn snipers
all around this area

544
00:42:07,192 --> 00:42:10,029
who would love to grease an officer.

545
00:42:10,112 --> 00:42:13,615
I'm Lieutenant Dan Taylor.
Welcome to Fourth Platoon.

546
00:42:14,491 --> 00:42:16,910
What's wrong with your lip?

547
00:42:16,994 --> 00:42:19,371
I was born with big gums, sir.

548
00:42:19,455 --> 00:42:24,168
Yeah, well, you better tuck that in.
Gonna get that caught on a trip wire.

549
00:42:25,335 --> 00:42:26,712
Where you boys from in the world?

550
00:42:26,795 --> 00:42:29,173
- Alabama, sir!
- Alabama, sir!

551
00:42:29,882 --> 00:42:31,383
You twins?

552
00:42:33,469 --> 00:42:35,888
No, we are not relations, sir.

553
00:42:38,140 --> 00:42:41,060
Look, it's pretty basic here.

554
00:42:41,852 --> 00:42:44,313
If you stick with me
and learn from the guys

555
00:42:44,396 --> 00:42:47,066
who've been in country a while,
you'll be all right.

556
00:42:47,149 --> 00:42:49,068
There is one item of GI gear

557
00:42:49,151 --> 00:42:53,322
that can be the difference between
a live grunt and a dead grunt.

558
00:42:53,655 --> 00:42:56,825
Socks. Cushion sole, OD green.

559
00:42:56,909 --> 00:42:58,202
Try and keep your feet dry.

560
00:42:58,327 --> 00:42:59,745
When we're out humping,
I want you boys to remember

561
00:42:59,828 --> 00:43:02,289
to change your socks whenever we stop.

562
00:43:02,372 --> 00:43:05,334
The Mekong will eat a grunt's feet
right off his legs.

563
00:43:05,417 --> 00:43:07,711
Sergeant Sims, God damn it,

564
00:43:07,836 --> 00:43:09,254
where is that sling rope
I told you to order?

565
00:43:09,338 --> 00:43:11,256
I put in the requisitions at Battalion.

566
00:43:11,340 --> 00:43:13,342
DAN: Yeah, yeah, yeah, well,
you call those sons of bitches again...

567
00:43:13,425 --> 00:43:15,969
<i>FORREST: Lieutenant Dan
sure knew his stuff.</i>

568
00:43:16,053 --> 00:43:18,347
<i>I felt real lucky he was my lieutenant.</i>

569
00:43:19,098 --> 00:43:22,559
<i>He was from a long,
great military tradition.</i>

570
00:43:22,768 --> 00:43:25,854
<i>Somebody in his family
had fought and died</i>

571
00:43:26,855 --> 00:43:31,110
<i>in every single American war.</i>

572
00:43:32,027 --> 00:43:34,029
- God damn it, kick some ass!
- I'm on it, Lieutenant.

573
00:43:34,113 --> 00:43:35,239
Get on it!

574
00:43:35,364 --> 00:43:38,700
<i>I guess you could say he had
a lot to live up to.</i>

575
00:43:40,410 --> 00:43:45,249
So, you boys are from Arkansas, huh?
Well, I've been through there.

576
00:43:45,374 --> 00:43:47,543
Little Rock's a fine town.

577
00:43:48,210 --> 00:43:51,797
Now, go shake down your gear,
see the platoon sergeant,

578
00:43:51,880 --> 00:43:54,341
draw what you need for the field.

579
00:43:54,424 --> 00:43:58,387
If you boys are hungry,
we got steaks burning right over here.

580
00:43:58,470 --> 00:44:01,348
Two standing orders in this platoon:

581
00:44:01,431 --> 00:44:04,101
one, take good care of your feet,

582
00:44:04,226 --> 00:44:09,273
two, try not to do anything stupid,
like getting yourself killed.

583
00:44:15,737 --> 00:44:17,823
I sure hope I don't let him down.

584
00:44:29,418 --> 00:44:31,920
<i>FORREST: I got to see
a lot of the countryside.</i>

585
00:44:32,004 --> 00:44:34,339
<i>We would take these real long walks.</i>

586
00:44:42,806 --> 00:44:46,935
<i>And we were always looking
for this guy named Charlie.</i>

587
00:44:54,776 --> 00:44:57,029
DAN: Hold it up!
SOLDIER: Hold up, boys!

588
00:44:59,865 --> 00:45:02,201
<i>It wasn't always fun.</i>

589
00:45:02,284 --> 00:45:06,580
<i>Lieutenant Dan was always getting
these funny feelings about a rock,</i>

590
00:45:06,663 --> 00:45:11,752
<i>or a trail, or the road,
so he'd tell us to get down, shut up...</i>

591
00:45:11,835 --> 00:45:13,837
Get down! Shut up!

592
00:45:14,796 --> 00:45:16,256
<i>(WHISPERING)...so we did.</i>

593
00:45:33,815 --> 00:45:35,984
<i>Now, I don't know much about anything,</i>

594
00:45:36,068 --> 00:45:39,905
<i>but I think some of America's
best young men served in this war.</i>

595
00:45:39,988 --> 00:45:42,699
<i>There was Dallas, from Phoenix,</i>

596
00:45:44,409 --> 00:45:47,204
<i>Cleveland, he was from Detroit.</i>

597
00:45:47,329 --> 00:45:49,706
(WHISPERING) Hey, Tex. Hey, Tex.

598
00:45:49,831 --> 00:45:52,000
Man, what the hell's going on?

599
00:45:52,084 --> 00:45:56,421
<i>And Tex was... Well, I don't remember
where Tex come from.</i>

600
00:45:56,505 --> 00:45:58,048
DAN: Nothing.

601
00:46:02,177 --> 00:46:04,680
Fourth Platoon, on your feet.

602
00:46:04,763 --> 00:46:08,475
Still got 10 klicks to go to that river.
Move out.

603
00:46:08,558 --> 00:46:10,352
Come on, move out.

604
00:46:12,396 --> 00:46:14,815
Step it up. Look alive out there.

605
00:46:14,898 --> 00:46:19,236
<i>The good thing about Vietnam
is there was always some place to go.</i>

606
00:46:19,361 --> 00:46:20,737
DAN: Fire in the hole!

607
00:46:24,199 --> 00:46:26,535
Gump, check out that hole.

608
00:46:26,618 --> 00:46:29,621
<i>And there was always something to do.</i>

609
00:46:29,705 --> 00:46:32,874
- Mount them up.
- SOLDIER: Spread out! Cover his back.

610
00:46:37,921 --> 00:46:43,552
<i>One day, it started raining,
and it didn't quit for four months.</i>

611
00:46:44,553 --> 00:46:47,431
<i>We'd been through
every kind of rain there is:</i>

612
00:46:47,556 --> 00:46:50,100
<i>little bitty stinging rain,</i>

613
00:46:50,809 --> 00:46:53,478
<i>and big old fat rain,</i>

614
00:46:53,937 --> 00:46:56,648
<i>rain that flew in sideways.</i>

615
00:46:56,732 --> 00:47:00,777
<i>And sometimes, rain even seemed
to come straight up from underneath.</i>

616
00:47:02,571 --> 00:47:04,948
<i>Shoot, it even rained at night.</i>

617
00:47:05,991 --> 00:47:08,452
- Hey, Forrest.
- Hey, Bubba.

618
00:47:08,577 --> 00:47:11,872
I'm gonna lean up against you.
You just lean right back against me.

619
00:47:11,955 --> 00:47:15,792
This way, we don't have to sleep
with our heads in the mud.

620
00:47:16,752 --> 00:47:20,213
You know why we a good partnership,
Forrest?

621
00:47:20,297 --> 00:47:22,799
'Cause we be watching out
for one another,

622
00:47:22,924 --> 00:47:24,801
like brothers and stuff.

623
00:47:26,762 --> 00:47:30,432
Hey, Forrest, there's something
I've been thinking about.

624
00:47:30,515 --> 00:47:33,518
I got a very important question
to ask you.

625
00:47:35,145 --> 00:47:39,107
How would you like to go
into the shrimping business with me?

626
00:47:40,275 --> 00:47:41,902
Okay.

627
00:47:41,985 --> 00:47:45,447
Man, I tell you what,
I got it all figured out, too.

628
00:47:45,530 --> 00:47:48,325
So many pounds of shrimp
to pay off the boat,

629
00:47:48,450 --> 00:47:51,745
so many pounds for gas,
we can just live right on the boat.

630
00:47:51,828 --> 00:47:54,122
We ain't got to pay no rent.

631
00:47:54,206 --> 00:47:56,291
I'll be the captain,
we can just work it together,

632
00:47:56,375 --> 00:48:00,629
split everything right down the middle.
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50.

633
00:48:00,712 --> 00:48:04,299
And, hey, Forrest,
all the shrimp you can eat.

634
00:48:05,842 --> 00:48:07,636
That's a fine idea.

635
00:48:08,720 --> 00:48:10,847
<i>FORREST: Bubba did have a fine idea.</i>

636
00:48:14,643 --> 00:48:17,729
<i>I even wrote Jenny
and told her all about it.</i>

637
00:48:18,522 --> 00:48:21,733
<i>I sent her letters,
not every day, but almost.</i>

638
00:48:21,817 --> 00:48:26,822
<i>I told her what I was doing
and asked her what she was doing,</i>

639
00:48:26,905 --> 00:48:29,658
<i>and told her
how I thought about her always,</i>

640
00:48:30,992 --> 00:48:33,954
<i>and how I was looking forward
to getting a letter from her</i>

641
00:48:34,037 --> 00:48:36,540
<i>just as soon as she had the time.</i>

642
00:48:38,417 --> 00:48:40,919
<i>I'd always let her know that I was okay.</i>

643
00:48:42,212 --> 00:48:47,384
<i>Then, I'd sign each letter,
"Love, Forrest Gump."</i>

644
00:49:02,232 --> 00:49:05,986
<i>This one day, we was out walking,
like always,</i>

645
00:49:06,069 --> 00:49:09,030
<i>and then, just like that,</i>

646
00:49:09,948 --> 00:49:13,368
<i>somebody turned off the rain
and the sun come out.</i>

647
00:49:16,371 --> 00:49:18,206
DAN: Ambush!

648
00:49:18,707 --> 00:49:20,083
Take cover!

649
00:49:20,250 --> 00:49:21,626
(GUNS FIRING)

650
00:49:23,712 --> 00:49:24,880
Get down!

651
00:49:24,963 --> 00:49:26,423
Get the sixty!

652
00:49:29,593 --> 00:49:31,678
Get that pig up here, God damn it!

653
00:49:31,761 --> 00:49:33,889
Forrest, you okay?

654
00:49:37,100 --> 00:49:39,728
Strongarm! Strongarm!
Be advised, Strongarm!

655
00:49:40,270 --> 00:49:42,689
Medic, we got a man down!

656
00:49:42,772 --> 00:49:45,734
Strongarm, this is Leg Lima 6, over!

657
00:49:46,443 --> 00:49:49,779
Roger, Strongarm, be advised
we have incoming from the tree line

658
00:49:49,905 --> 00:49:53,408
at points blue plus two.
AKs and rockets...

659
00:49:54,075 --> 00:49:55,869
Misfire! Misfire!

660
00:49:58,246 --> 00:50:00,248
DAN: God damn it! Mac!

661
00:50:01,208 --> 00:50:04,628
Get that thing...
Fuck it, get it in the tree line!

662
00:50:05,587 --> 00:50:06,755
Jesus!

663
00:50:06,880 --> 00:50:09,090
My unit is down hard and hurting!

664
00:50:09,216 --> 00:50:12,761
Six are pulling back to Blue Line,
Leg Lima 6 out.

665
00:50:13,553 --> 00:50:15,514
Pull back! Pull back!

666
00:50:15,597 --> 00:50:17,724
Run! Run, Forrest!

667
00:50:17,807 --> 00:50:20,143
- Pull back!
- BUBBA: Forrest, Forrest!

668
00:50:20,268 --> 00:50:22,854
Run, man! Run!

669
00:50:22,938 --> 00:50:24,731
DAN: Pull back! Run!

670
00:50:26,566 --> 00:50:28,777
Run, God damn it, run!

671
00:50:49,965 --> 00:50:54,594
SOLDIER: Medic! Can I get a medic?

672
00:50:54,970 --> 00:50:58,306
<i>FORREST: I ran and ran,
just like Jenny told me to.</i>

673
00:51:01,685 --> 00:51:05,897
<i>I ran so far and so fast
that pretty soon I was all by myself,</i>

674
00:51:05,981 --> 00:51:07,941
<i>which was a bad thing.</i>

675
00:51:08,483 --> 00:51:10,026
Bubba!

676
00:51:12,153 --> 00:51:15,949
<i>Bubba was my best good friend.
I had to make sure that he was okay.</i>

677
00:51:19,661 --> 00:51:21,705
SOLDIER 1: Any friendlies out there?

678
00:51:22,664 --> 00:51:24,833
SOLDIER 2: Yeah, I've got
three over here.

679
00:51:25,458 --> 00:51:27,460
Where the hell are you?

680
00:51:28,044 --> 00:51:29,379
Bubba?

681
00:51:30,463 --> 00:51:33,174
<i>And on my way back to find Bubba,</i>

682
00:51:33,300 --> 00:51:36,094
<i>well, there was this boy
laying on the ground.</i>

683
00:51:36,177 --> 00:51:37,387
Tex!

684
00:51:39,472 --> 00:51:40,473
Okay.

685
00:51:40,557 --> 00:51:44,519
<i>I couldn't just let him lay there all alone,
scared the way he was,</i>

686
00:51:44,644 --> 00:51:48,523
<i>so I grabbed him up
and run him out of there.</i>

687
00:52:03,663 --> 00:52:06,082
<i>And every time I went back
looking for Bubba,</i>

688
00:52:06,207 --> 00:52:09,711
<i>somebody else was saying,
"Help me, Forrest. Help me."</i>

689
00:52:17,385 --> 00:52:19,262
Can't hear... Can't hear...

690
00:52:21,556 --> 00:52:22,849
SOLDIER: No sweat, man. Just lay back.

691
00:52:22,932 --> 00:52:25,435
